-- SHADOW-SEMANTICS cell I6 (matrix row 21a): IMPORTER shadow in VALUE position over
-- NO-IMPL elements.  S4 is not keyed on where the standalone lives, so this is the
-- importer twin of d4 and its expectation is IDENTICAL (row 21 "expected = row 9"):
-- the bare `size` denotes the imported STANDALONE, so `map size [1, 2, 3]` = [2, 3, 4].
--
-- #411: was a LOUD S7 split -- check accepted and run printed [2, 3, 4], but BUILD
-- died `no impl of method 'size' for type 'Int' (slice 6)` with no binary, because the
-- importer shadow set did not survive mangling (standaloneShadowsFromSet had no
-- mangled-recovery arm), so resolveArgStamp's RKey Int clobbered the mark pass's
-- correct RLocal seed.  Pin the VALUE, not the exit code: all three paths agreeing is
-- exactly what this cell cannot rely on (S7).
-- Expected: check accepts; run/build print [2, 3, 4].
import prov.{size}

data Box = Box Int

interface Sizeable a where
  size : a -> Int

impl Sizeable Box where
  size (Box n) = n

main = println (map size [1, 2, 3])
